  "prompt": "What are the best side dishes for fried shrimp?",
  "response": "Fried shrimp is a versatile dish that pairs well with a variety of side dishes. Here are some of the best options to complement its flavor and texture:\n\n### **Light and Fresh Sides**\n1. **Coleslaw** \u2013 A crisp, tangy coleslaw provides a refreshing contrast to the richness of fried shrimp.\n2. **Green Salad** \u2013 A simple green salad with a light vinaigrette adds freshness and balance.\n3. **Cucumber Salad** \u2013 Thinly sliced cucumbers with a vinegar-based dressing is crisp and refreshing.\n4. **Avocado Salad** \u2013 Creamy avocado with tomatoes, red onion, and a lime dressing adds richness without overwhelming the shrimp.\n\n### **Starchy Sides**\n5. **French Fries** \u2013 Classic and always a crowd-pleaser, fries are a perfect match for fried shrimp.\n6. **Hush Puppies** \u2013 These cornmeal fritters are a Southern staple that pairs wonderfully with fried shrimp.\n7. **Mashed Potatoes** \u2013 Creamy mashed potatoes provide a comforting, hearty side.\n8. **Rice Pilaf** \u2013 Fluffy, seasoned rice is a great way to soak up any extra sauce or flavor.\n9. **Sweet Potato Fries** \u2013 A slightly sweet and crispy alternative to traditional fries.\n\n### **Vegetable Sides**\n10. **Grilled Asparagus** \u2013 Lightly charred asparagus adds a smoky, fresh element.\n11. **Corn on the Cob** \u2013 Sweet, buttery corn is a classic pairing with fried shrimp.\n12. **Roasted Vegetables** \u2013 A mix of roasted zucchini, bell peppers, and carrots adds color and flavor.\n13. **Steamed Broccoli** \u2013 Simple and healthy, steamed broccoli complements fried shrimp without overpowering it.\n\n### **Dips and Sauces**\n14. **Cocktail Sauce** \u2013 A tangy, tomato-based sauce is a classic accompaniment.\n15. **Tartar Sauce** \u2013 Creamy and tangy, tartar sauce is a must for fried shrimp.\n16. **Remoulade** \u2013 A zesty, slightly spicy sauce that adds a kick of flavor.\n17. **Garlic Aioli** \u2013 A rich, garlicky dip that pairs beautifully with fried shrimp.\n\n### **Other Creative Options**\n18. **Mac and Cheese** \u2013 Creamy, cheesy mac and cheese is a comforting and indulgent side.\n19. **Fried Okra** \u2013 A Southern favorite that complements the crispy texture of fried shrimp.\n20. **Garlic Bread** \u2013 Warm, buttery garlic bread is great for soaking up any extra sauce.\n\nMix and match these sides based on your preferences and the occasion!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
